🚀 ANSIBLE COMPLETE ROADMAP (ZERO TO HERO – FULL INDEX)
🟢 PHASE 0: HISTORY + WHY ANSIBLE (VERY IMPORTANT)
0.1 History of Ansible
Created by Michael DeHaan (2012)
Later acquired by Red Hat
Now part of Red Hat Automation Platform
0.2 Why Ansible was created?

Before Ansible:

Manual server configuration
SSH scripts (Bash scripts)
Complex tools like Puppet/Chef

Problems:

Complex setup
Agent installation needed
Hard learning curve

👉 Solution: Ansible = simple + agentless automation

0.3 Why Ansible is used?
Server automation
Configuration management
Application deployment
Cloud automation
Infrastructure automation
0.4 Ansible Key Features
Agentless (NO software on remote servers)
SSH based
YAML easy language
Idempotent (safe repeated execution)
Simple & human readable
0.5 Comparison with Other Tools
🟡 Ansible vs Puppet
Feature	Ansible	Puppet
Agent	No	Yes
Language	YAML	DSL
Complexity	Easy	Medium
Setup	Simple	Complex
🟡 Ansible vs Chef
Feature	Ansible	Chef
Language	YAML	Ruby
Setup	Easy	Complex
Learning	Easy	Hard
🟡 Ansible vs Terraform
Feature	Ansible	Terraform
Purpose	Configuration	Infrastructure provisioning
Focus	Servers setup	Cloud resources
Language	YAML	HCL
🟡 Ansible vs Shell Scripts
Feature	Ansible	Shell
Readability	High	Low
Reusability	High	Low
Structure	Strong	Weak
